The paper deals with the Firing Squad Synchronization Problem (FSSP) for P systems, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph theory (cs.DS). The use of strongly connected digraphs and awareness of local topology also suggests a connection to graph algorithms and complexity (cs.LO). The problem of synchronization is also relevant to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL). Finally, the paper proposes a solution that involves communication and coordination, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY).
